  "title": "Welding Engineer @ Jurong Island",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Prepare, qualify, and submit Welding Procedures per applicable codes, standards, and project requirements for client and third-party approval.</li><li>Supervise welding teams (supervisors, inspectors, foremen, welders) to ensure compliance and optimal performance.</li><li>Review material certifications, welding consumables, and maintain Welding Procedures records project-wise.</li><li>Verify and ensure compliance of welding and testing reports</li><li>Collaborate with QA/QC to develop documentation (Inspection Test Plan, work instructions, welding/NDT maps, MDR, NCRs).</li><li>Implement updates to codes/standards (ASME, API, AWS, BS, EN) across relevant departments.</li><li>Ensure adherence to project quality standards, QMS, and client requirements.</li><li>Investigate non-conformances, perform root cause analysis, and recommend corrective actions.</li><li>Expertise in WPS/PQR preparation for various materials (CS, SS, DSS, Inconel, aluminum).</li><li>Knowledge of various welding processes and joint design optimization.</li><li>Liaise with third-party inspectors and auditors for audits.</li><li>Optimize welding techniques for efficiency and quality in workshop/site welding.</li><li>Monitor welder performance, rejection rates, and conduct root cause analysis failures.</li><li>Develop welding methods to enhance production workflow.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Must be well-versed with ASME codes, particularly:</li></ul><ol><li>ASME BPVC Section I (Power Boilers)</li><li>ASME B31.1 (Power Piping)</li></ol><ul><li>Including full understanding of PWHT (Post Weld Heat Treatment) requirements under these codes.</li><li>Experience in welding engineering and technical management for gas-fired power plant projects is highly preferred.</li><li>Plan and implement Post Welding Heat Treatment</li><li>This position is for Engineer who planned, supervised welding operations (NOT just QC Inspection)</li><li>Diploma/Degree in Mechanical Engineering or related vocational education</li><li>Min 5 years’ experience in welding works and as Welding Engineer is preferred</li><li>Possess certificate of AWS Certified Welding inspector (CWI) / CSWIP 3.2 is preferred OR ISO welding cert like International Welding Specialist (IWS)</li><li>Knowledge in codes ie ASME/AWS D1.1/ BS EN and ISO standard</li><li>Knowledge in various welding process is a MUST</li><li>Experience in Non-Destructive Testing is advantageous</li></ul>",
